OL,5,GTV schedules are now back to normal
OL,6,Gfollowing the period of mourning which
OL,7,Gfollowed the death of HM The Queen. But
OL,8,Gthere will be a legacy which is likely
OL,9,Gto be felt for several days.
OL,11,FThe main commercial channels suspended
OL,12,Fall advertising in the immediate
OL,13,Faftermath of The Queen's death.
OL,15,FThrough the period of mourning, there
OL,16,Fwas no advertising around programmes
OL,17,Fconcerning Her Majesty's death or the
OL,18,Ffuneral. Indeed advertising is
OL,19,Fspecifically forbidden during formal
OL,20,FRoyal events.
OL,3,CCommercial channels play catch-up with
OL,4,Cadverts
OL,22,                                   G1/6
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35202
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1667072492
OL,5,FHowever this means that more
OL,6,Fadvertising than normal is now being
OL,7,Fshown.
OL,9,FThe Code on the Scheduling of
OL,10,FTelevision Advertisements allows for
OL,11,Fthe transfer of lost advertising time
OL,12,Fin certain circumstances. This is just
OL,13,Fsuch a situation.
OL,15,FThe broadcasters will have approached
OL,16,FOfcom with a request to do this.
OL,18,FThe temporary increase in advertising
OL,19,Fis particularly noticeable on ITV.
OL,3,CCommercial channels play catch-up with
OL,4,Cadverts
OL,22,                                   G2/6
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35203
