PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1667072492
OL,5,FFor instance there is now a full 12
OL,6,Fminutes of advertising in the 3pm hour
OL,7,Fand an extra 4 minute break just before
OL,8,Fthe ITV Evening News at 6.30pm.
OL,10,FThe break before 9pm has also been
OL,11,Freconfigured  generally 90 seconds of
OL,12,Fadvertising Is running before 9pm and
OL,13,F90 seconds afterwards. Before, the
OL,14,Fbreak normally only lasted 90 seconds
OL,15,Fin total.
OL,17,FThis is being done, it seems, to allow
OL,18,Fan extra break of around 4 minutes
OL,19,Fbefore News at Ten which has
OL,20,Ftemporarily been billed at 10.05pm.
OL,3,CCommercial channels play catch-up with
OL,4,Cadverts
OL,22,                                   G3/6
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35204
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1667072492
OL,5,FThe main reason for moving things round
OL,6,Fso much is to ensure that no clock hour
OL,7,Fcontains more than 12 minutes of
OL,8,Fadverts.
OL,10,FWhile this is only temporary, it comes
OL,11,Fas Ofcom considers whether to allow
OL,12,FITV, Channel 4 and Channel 5 to run as
OL,13,Fmany adverts as other channels.
OL,15,FIf there if no adverse public reaction,
OL,16,Fit will suggest that the public might
OL,17,Faccept a permanent increase.
OL,3,CCommercial channels play catch-up with
OL,4,Cadverts
OL,22,                                   G4/6
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35205
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1667072492
OL,5,FThe decision is not a given  there is
OL,6,Fa risk that an increase in advertising
OL,7,Ftime could drive down prices so be of
OL,8,Fno benefit to broadcasters or viewers.
OL,9,FThat will need proper examination.
OL,11,FIt doesn't go without saying that a
OL,12,Fpermanent increase would be handled in
OL,13,Fthe same way on air. Programme
OL,14,Fdurations may need to be slightly
OL,15,Freduced to help keep the schedule
OL,16,Frunning to time.
OL,18,FOfcom's current consultation runs for
OL,19,Fanother fortnight.
